1
00:01:06,640 --> 00:01:07,280
Hold me tight.

2
00:01:39,880 --> 00:01:41,040
Is Lin Mojiao crazy?

3
00:01:41,720 --> 00:01:42,880
He's always been a lunatic.

4
00:01:50,560 --> 00:01:52,520
There's nothing in this remote area.

5
00:01:53,080 --> 00:01:54,120
What do we do now?

6
00:01:57,680 --> 00:01:58,480
Follow me.

7
00:01:59,080 --> 00:01:59,920
Don't touch me.

8
00:03:21,960 --> 00:03:23,360
These two are delicious.

9
00:03:23,520 --> 00:03:24,520
This starfruit
and the wax apple

10
00:03:25,360 --> 00:03:26,120
are very good.
This doesn't look authentic.

11
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:28,520
It's authentic.

12
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:29,920
You talk as if

13
00:03:29,920 --> 00:03:31,000
you are familiar with this place.

14
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:31,720
Buy, buy, buy.
Have a taste.

15
00:03:32,600 --> 00:03:33,320
It's delicious.

16
00:03:33,480 --> 00:03:34,640
It's tastier than the dipped one.

17
00:03:34,880 --> 00:03:35,640
Have a taste.

18
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:37,520
It's okay if you don't buy.

19
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:39,600
I'm hungry.
I want to eat.

20
00:03:42,880 --> 00:03:43,440
You try it.

21
00:03:44,280 --> 00:03:45,240
It's not fresh.

22
00:03:45,360 --> 00:03:45,920
If you want to eat seafood,

23
00:03:46,200 --> 00:03:47,040
you should go to the seaside.

24
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:51,720
We don't have money.

25
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:52,920
I'm tired and hungry now.

26
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:54,360
Where are you taking me?

27
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:55,760
We'll be there soon.

28
00:03:56,120 --> 00:03:56,480
Come on.

29
00:04:32,440 --> 00:04:33,520
Why did he come here?

30
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:36,440
What is this place?

31
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:02,800
Dad,

32
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:04,640
Mom,

33
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:09,000
I'll send my brother to see you soon.

34
00:05:13,080 --> 00:05:14,200
I almost forgot.

35
00:05:18,560 --> 00:05:21,000
I also prepared a daughter-in-law for you.

36
00:05:22,840 --> 00:05:24,600
You will be very happy.

37
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:48,040
Can I borrow your necklace?

38
00:06:49,760 --> 00:06:50,920
Can you do it?

39
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,040
Use this as collateral.

40
00:07:05,160 --> 00:07:05,960
One thousand.

41
00:07:10,520 --> 00:07:11,320
Five hundred.

42
00:07:12,320 --> 00:07:13,120
One thousand.

43
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:04,000
Place your bets.

44
00:08:20,520 --> 00:08:21,520
Please look at the cards.

45
00:08:34,600 --> 00:08:35,520
[Place your bets.]

46
00:08:58,920 --> 00:08:59,840
Bet you don't have a King.

47
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:08,960
Straight flush wins.

48
00:09:49,160 --> 00:09:49,680
Boss,

49
00:09:49,920 --> 00:09:52,120
someone deliberately disrupted the casino's rules.

50
00:09:52,440 --> 00:09:53,160
Maybe they're here to cause trouble.
Old rules.

51
00:09:54,160 --> 00:09:54,920
Yes.

52
00:09:58,800 --> 00:09:59,440
Enough.
Time to go.

53
00:10:00,840 --> 00:10:01,720
Leaving already?

54
00:10:37,360 --> 00:10:38,280
They're running back.

55
00:10:40,480 --> 00:10:41,400
Stop!

56
00:10:41,640 --> 00:10:42,360
Don't run!

57
00:10:43,360 --> 00:10:43,800
You guys go over there.
Okay.

58
00:10:50,520 --> 00:10:51,240
Are you okay?

59
00:10:56,320 --> 00:10:57,120
You're shy.

60
00:10:59,680 --> 00:11:00,240
I'm hungry.
Let's go eat.

61
00:11:14,960 --> 00:11:16,200
I'll show you around.

62
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:08,200
That looks good.
I want to eat that.

63
00:12:29,280 --> 00:12:29,640
How

64
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:31,680
How to play this?

65
00:12:32,720 --> 00:12:33,600
Take this ball

66
00:12:33,920 --> 00:12:35,200
to hit that board.

67
00:12:35,560 --> 00:12:37,120
Then these two boys will fall into the water.

68
00:12:37,680 --> 00:12:38,200
I want to play.

69
00:12:47,520 --> 00:12:48,040
Thank you.

70
00:13:00,240 --> 00:13:01,480
Yes, try that.

71
00:13:12,280 --> 00:13:13,520
I'll give you a doll.

72
00:13:16,720 --> 00:13:17,280
It's so ugly.
I don't want it.

73
00:13:18,880 --> 00:13:19,680
It's not ugly.

74
00:13:20,040 --> 00:13:21,360
Look, this doll is so much like you.

75
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:23,680
Annoying.

76
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:34,640
You seem to know this place very well.

77
00:13:37,480 --> 00:13:38,320
Many people know that

78
00:13:38,320 --> 00:13:39,840
the second son of the Lin family is abroad.

79
00:13:40,720 --> 00:13:42,000
But no one cares

80
00:13:42,120 --> 00:13:43,280
why I stay abroad.

81
00:13:46,680 --> 00:13:47,640
After my father died,

82
00:13:49,480 --> 00:13:51,080
Lin Mojiao was very concerned about me,

83
00:13:51,400 --> 00:13:52,680
chasing me all the way abroad.

84
00:13:52,920 --> 00:13:54,960
He also taught me a lot of survival skills.

85
00:14:08,040 --> 00:14:09,480
Where did this little brat run off to?

86
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:10,760
Forget it.

87
00:14:10,920 --> 00:14:12,240
A kid that young fell into the sea.

88
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:13,240
He must be dead.

89
00:14:14,280 --> 00:14:14,760
Let's go.
Go, go, go.

90
00:15:10,520 --> 00:15:10,800
One.

91
00:15:11,960 --> 00:15:12,280
Two.

92
00:15:13,320 --> 00:15:13,640
Three.

93
00:15:15,400 --> 00:15:15,800
Four.

94
00:15:17,680 --> 00:15:18,040
Five.

95
00:15:19,720 --> 00:15:20,120
Six.

96
00:15:22,240 --> 00:15:22,640
Seven.

97
00:15:28,240 --> 00:15:29,160
I'm sorry.

98
00:15:30,280 --> 00:15:31,880
I didn't know you went through all this.

99
00:15:33,560 --> 00:15:34,720
I thought you hated him

100
00:15:34,800 --> 00:15:36,640
just for fighting over the inheritance.

101
00:15:37,800 --> 00:15:38,600
Turns out,

102
00:15:38,920 --> 00:15:39,520
what he did to you

103
00:15:39,520 --> 00:15:40,920
was even worse than I imagined.

104
00:15:41,960 --> 00:15:42,680
It's okay.

105
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:44,800
Actually,

106
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:46,920
none of this matters.

107
00:15:48,160 --> 00:15:48,960
After all,

108
00:15:50,960 --> 00:15:52,000
I made all this

109
00:15:57,680 --> 00:15:58,320
up.

110
00:16:04,400 --> 00:16:05,480
You're so naive.

111
00:16:05,760 --> 00:16:06,640
You actually believe that?

112
00:16:14,280 --> 00:16:15,960
Were you feeling sorry for me just now?

113
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:21,560
Have you ever heard a saying?

114
00:16:21,960 --> 00:16:22,640
What?

115
00:16:25,760 --> 00:16:26,960
Feeling sorry for a man

116
00:16:27,560 --> 00:16:29,000
is the beginning of misfortune.

117
00:16:38,440 --> 00:16:39,560
Why did you buy a cake?

118
00:16:40,640 --> 00:16:41,280
I just saw it.
It's not bad.

119
00:16:47,960 --> 00:16:48,840
What are you doing?

120
00:16:50,360 --> 00:16:51,400
You gave me the whole set.

121
00:16:51,960 --> 00:16:52,600
Don't waste it.
Make a wish.

122
00:17:09,720 --> 00:17:10,440
What's wrong?

123
00:17:20,360 --> 00:17:20,960
Happy birthday.
